@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container py-4" style="max-width: 900px;">

    <div class="mb-4">
        <h1 class="h3 mb-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <div class="text-muted small">
            DigitalisationManager
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0">
        <div class="card-body p-4">

            <p class="text-muted mb-4">
                DigitalisationManager is a platform for accessing and working with digitised archival materials.
                This Privacy Policy explains what information may be processed when you use the site and how that
                information is handled within the system.
            </p>

            <h2 class="h5">1. Use of the Platform</h2>
            <p>
                The platform allows authorised users to sign in, browse archival funds, review items, and access
                available digital files. The information presented through the site is intended to support structured
                access to archival materials in a clear and secure environment.
            </p>

            <h2 class="h5 mt-4">2. Account and Access Information</h2>
            <p>
                When you use the platform, your account information may be processed for authentication and access control.
                This is used only to identify authorised users and to provide access to the appropriate parts of the system.
            </p>

            <h2 class="h5 mt-4">3. Information Available in the System</h2>
            <p>
                The platform may display archival information such as funds, items, descriptions, dates, and related
                digital materials. This information is managed within the system in order to make archival content easier
                to organise, review, and access.
            </p>

            <h2 class="h5 mt-4">4. Digital Files</h2>
            <p>
                Some records may include associated digital files. Access to these files is provided through the platform
                only to users with the appropriate permissions.
            </p>

            <h2 class="h5 mt-4">5. Protection of Information</h2>
            <p>
                Reasonable technical and organisational measures are used to help protect information processed through the
                platform and to limit access to authorised users only.
            </p>

            <h2 class="h5 mt-4">6. Appropriate Use</h2>
            <p>
                Users are expected to use the platform responsibly and only for lawful and appropriate purposes. Unauthorised
                attempts to access, copy, alter, or misuse data or digital materials are not permitted.
            </p>

            <h2 class="h5 mt-4">7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                This Privacy Policy may be updated when needed to reflect changes in the platform or its operation.
                Continued use of the site after an update means that the revised policy applies.
            </p>

            <h2 class="h5 mt-4">8. Contact</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
                If you have questions about privacy or the use of this platform, please contact the organisation
                responsible for the system or the site administrator.
            </p>

        </div>
    </div>

</div>